    <bioghist encodinganalog="545$a">
      <head>Historical Information
</head>
      <p>Cumberland County was named for William Augustus, duke of Cumberland, third son of King George II. It was formed from Goochland County in 1749. The county seat is Cumberland. 
</p>
      </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
      <head>Scope and Content
</head>
      <p>Cumberland County (Va.) Apprenticeship Indentures, 1759-1857, are bonds and contracts of apprenticeship, showing the names of master and apprentice, the trade to be taught, details of the contract, the amount of the bond and the names of sureties. Many of the apprentices bound out prior to 1866 were free African Americans.
</p>
    </scopecontent>
